Essential tool for my Benelli TreK. I use it to troubleshoot, reset the TPS, log engine fuel management data and make EFI map adjustments. TuneECU makes TreK ownership much easier and saves a fortune! For example without it I would have to take my bike 200km to town and find someone equipped and competent to do jobs TuneECU enables me to do at home. A Lonelec cable is available to connect OTG capable Android devices but I use 1/. an AMP 6 Pin Superseal to DB9 adapter assembled according to the instructions on the TuneECU website. 2/. A UT-880 USB to RS 232 adapter cable (FTDI FT232RL chipset). 3/. An OTG adapter cable (USB-A socket to Micro-B Plug). The FT232RL adapter cable is automatically detected by TuneECU for Android (note this is the only cable that works properly for Android). It connects quickly when "Connect" is selected from the "ECU" menu (with the bike ignition and kill switches in the on position). I do not have an Android device with simultaneous data communication and charge capability so I use the Windows version for map updates. A 10 amp battery charger on the bike and charger on the PC prevent potential low voltage. That avoids the risk of communication failure while writing to the ECU and a hassle I would rather not face.

This app is absolutely fantastic. I have just rebuilt and fixed a project bike. This app let me log the first warm up after head gasket and cooling system replacement. I fixed the idle speed issues by relearning stepper motor. Cleared fault codes, ran tests. Best tenner I spent in a long time!

content: I paid $12.94 for and installed this app on an ASUS Transformer tablet.  I connected it to the OBD2 cable via USB to my KTM690 Enduro.  Finally the app started to read my FI map from my bike, but it just hung at 78% read and never got finished.  So, I started over and selected the EF map.  It was slow, but got to 99% and when I thought it was going to finish, the app just crashed and put up an error message.  Nothing useful, and it totally failed on the read function!  I did not get to save my stock maps. Glad this app showed how bad it was BEFORE I tried to download new maps to my bike.  Don't waste your effort and money on this app!  I can't rate it negative stars, or else I would!
Been using the pic version since it's conception and bought this tablet just for this purpose love your work Allan
